snippet.title: "Freedom of Speech" - Marsh Family parody of "Under the Sea" from Disney's "The Little Mermaid"
snippet.description:
We couldn't find any lobster costumes, and a whirling freestyle in the middle of a school week was not gonna happen. So - with some extra input from a few media sources to cover instrumental sections - this is our parody rendition of "Under the Sea", one of our old Disney favourites for its sheer joy and energy. It was composed by Alan Menken (with cracking lyrics by Howard Ashman) for the 1989 animated "The Little Mermaid" and won an Oscar. Of course, the calypso lobster's forlorn plea for an alternative path falls on deaf ears. Which brings us to free speech.

It's been a scary time in lots of ways in the US, with the temperature cranked up again by shocking murders and reckless responses, and sadly now the First Amendment (for decades a place of some bipartisan accord) seems to be creaking. As we were working on the arrangement, we learned that Jimmy Kimmel's show had been reinstated by Disney - which is great news, having loved meeting him in 2020 albeit under bizarre pandemic circumstances - though we gather that much is still unclear about how the matter is going to play out. Here's hoping that enough uproar is generated that Trump and co. think again about making their predictable/alarming move on limiting freedom of expression. 

We're assuming folk will have enough pointers not to need links, but will keep an eye on comments and can fill in any details!

P.S. Please note: for anyone whose kids watch, Ben forget to put special characters in the swear word at the death of the song, so heads-up on that.

LYRICS:

We see that the US media
Is facing a service break
The satirists being shut up there
By censorship of the state
What’s up with the First Amendment?
Got speared in the culture war!
The time for the jokes has ended
George Orwell’s back in the drawer!

Freedom of speech
Freedom of speech
It’s a dead letter
When you upset the 
Autocracy
Used to define the USA
Now gotta watch out what you say!
Don’t be critiquing
Or public speaking
Nod and agree

A smear might make you unhappy
There’s insults from bots and trolls
Abuse, when it lands, feels crappy
(I had to look up “cuckold”!)
But if you get slurred as “Nazi”
And want to retaliate
It’s not the best self-defence, see,
To mimic a fascist state (uh oh!)

Freedom of speech
Freedom of speech
No more displeasing, only appeasing the FCC
They say it’s “easy way or hard”
He’s such a teaser, Brendon Carr!
Wielding his muzzle
Networks don’t struggle
Heel on the leash

Hypocrisy (hypocrisy!)
Hypocrisy (hypocrisy!)
Free speech believers 
Pulling the levers
Of the “thought police”
Using the regulator’s sway
Pressuring outlets what to say
Kimmel, near cancelled …
Colbert dismantled …
Goebbels-style glee

The left like to carp
The right like to bait
There’s truth in some lies
There’s threat in some hate
There’s innocent barbs
There’s hooks that incite
It’s hard trying to find the line (Yeah!)
In history’s eyes
The ratings are in:
The sicker the mind,
The thinner the skin
From Caesar to Mao
From Stalin to now
Their ego’s quick to blow

Yeah, freedom of speech (fire in the breach)
Freedom of speech (fire in the breach)
When it gets weaker
You can browbeat a
Democracy
Just when you need a calmer stance
Up pops red hot Vice President Vance
Gives Europe sermons
While he pulls U-turns
Freedom of speech
Making things ‘great’ there
Stifling debate there
Freedom of speech

Each little measure
Building the pressure
Cow all the papers
Rat out your neighbours
Wish you all luck there
Seems pretty f&*ked there!
Freedom of speech

snippet.title: Call of Duty: Black Ops 7 | Multiplayer Gameplay Reveal Trailer

What is Roblox? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It’s unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX — interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

snippet.title: Peaky Blinders: The Immortal Man (2026) - First Trailer | Cillian Murphy - Concept
snippet.description:
#peakyblinders #cillianmurphy #theimmortalman 

Watch This: "PEAKY BLINDERS: THE IMMORTAL MAN – Fan-Made Concept Trailer"

A legend never dies… but what if he never could?

In this dark live-action fan-made concept trailer, Cillian Murphy returns as Thomas Shelby in a story that takes the Peaky Blinders legacy into a supernatural realm. After surviving countless wars, betrayals, and battles, Thomas discovers the truth — he cannot die. Gifted, or cursed, with immortality, he becomes The Immortal Man.

But eternity has its price. As decades pass, enemies rise and fall, yet new threats emerge from the shadows — some mortal, some not. Haunted by his family’s legacy and the blood on his hands, Thomas must confront a destiny far greater than Birmingham’s streets: to fight the hidden war that spans across centuries.

From smoky alleys and roaring 1920s streets, to gothic ruins and timeless battlegrounds, this trailer reimagines Peaky Blinders with an immortal twist, blending crime, history, and supernatural myth.

When time is endless… power becomes the deadliest weapon.

snippet.description:
#terminator #terminator7finalwar #arnoldschwarzenegger 

Schwarzenegger leads humanity in Terminator’s final chapter. 

Editing, VFX, SFX, Thumbnail by @KHStudio please subscribe:
✅ YouTube: https://bit.ly/KHstudio

🎥 Attention viewers!

Please note that this video is a concept trailer created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes. I have meticulously incorporated various effects, sound design, AI technologies (Google Veo 3), movie analytics, and other elements to bring my vision to life. Its purpose is purely artistic, aiming to entertain and engage with the YouTube community. My goal is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through this trailer. Thank you for your support, and let's dive into the world of imagination! 🍿

🤖  Terminator 7: Final War

Speculation is mounting that Terminator 7: Final War may be in development, with Arnold Schwarzenegger rumored to reprise his legendary role one final time. The project is said to bring the decades-long battle between humanity and Skynet to a dramatic conclusion, closing the chapter on one of science fiction’s most iconic franchises. Schwarzenegger’s possible return has generated widespread attention, with many believing this could serve as both a farewell to the character and a definitive finale to the series.

Whispers about the story suggest that Final War will take place in a timeline where the resistance has gained significant ground, setting up a climactic confrontation between man and machine. snippet.title: HAQ | Official Teaser | Yami Gautam Dhar, Emraan Hashmi | Suparn S Varma | In Cinemas 7th Nov
snippet.description:
Shazia Bano takes her husband Abbas to court after he abandons her and their children, sparking a national battle over faith, women’s rights, and justice. Inspired by the landmark Supreme Court judgement of Mohd. Ahmed Khan vs. Shah Bano Begum. Haq is the story of one woman’s fight for her rights and justice. 

Releasing in cinemas on 7th November

HAQ is a fictionalized and dramatized version of events stated in the book titled ‘Bano: Bharat ki Beti’ written by Jigna Vora.

Cast- Yami Gautam, Emraan Hashmi, Vartika Singh, Danish Husain, Sheeba Chadha,
Aseem Hattangady
Directed by- Suparn S Varma
Written by- Reshu Nath
Produced by- Vineet Jain
Produced by- Vishal Gurnani, Juhi Parekh Mehta, Harman Baweja
Co- Producer- Amrita Pandey
Co-Producer- Suparn S Varma, Rowena Baweja, Sandeep Singh
Supervising Producer- Vicky Jain

Director of Photography- Pratham Mehta
Associate Producer- Kalpesh Damani
Supervising Producer- Shraddha Chauhan
Executive Producers- Ramesh G Yadav, Priyanka Mehrotra
Production Designers- Abhijit Gaonkar, Sonam Singh

Chief Finance Officer- Mukesh Jain
